B15 -  Teach an elderly person about cybersecurity topic of your choice

Objective
The goal of this activity was to educate an elderly individual about basic cybersecurity concepts to improve their awareness of online risks.

Method
I explained key cybersecurity concepts to an elderly individual throguh a simple verbal discussion, followed by a reinforcement message. The explanation focused on real-life scenarios such as scam messages and account security.

Content covered
1. Phishing/scam messages - I explained how scammers send fae messages pretending to be trusted organisations to steal personal information
2. One-time Passwords/MFA - I explained that verification codes sent to a phone should never be shared with anyone.
3. Basic online safety - I emphasized being cautious when receiving unexpected messages or links.

Outcome
The individual gained a better understanding of common online scams and became more aware of not sharing sensitive information such as OTP codes.

Relfection
This activity showed that simple awareness can significantly improve cybersecurity for individuals who may not be familiar with digital risks. It also helped me improve my ability to explain cybersecurity concepts in a clear and practical way.
